Package com.example.hashcache.models

Class CodeMetadata

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.example.hashcache.models.CodeMetadata
  • public class CodeMetadata
extends java.lang.Object
    A class representing metadata for a scannable code. This metadata includes the code's document ID, scannable code ID, location (represented as a GeoLocation and geohash), and image (if available). This class uses the Firebase GeoFireUtils library to obtain a geohash for a given location. It also uses the SHA-256 algorithm to generate a unique document ID based on the scannable code ID and geohash.
